camp is completely open, we are fighting in hall when here comes an iksar monk, Morin, tearing past us with a frog in tow. It, of course, adds to our fight..well, no big deal..but I have this strange feeling in my stomach. Where was that monk goin in such a hurry when there are no people in disco? I quickly find out, he is pulling! Yay, right thru a group he brings ALL the rest of the hall, plus the interior mobs from disco! Woot, can you say death to the wizzy who was tryin to evac? I know you can boys and girls. Chanter manages to mez the 12 mobs, the rest of us evac, I pull wizzy's corpse to entrance and then I zone with 10 life...<br><br>I zone back in, ask Morin &quot;WTF?&quot; He can't be a man and admit his mistake..NOOO, wouldn't be prudent, he's a MONK! Of course we have to go through the whole rigamorale..&quot;No, I didn't train anyone, I'm near chef, heh&quot;..&quot;Well, I might have pulled thru a group earlier, I don't know, do you need help with CR?&quot; &quot;Chill out dude&quot; etc etc...I'm starting to get that eyelash twitch as visions of KC run thru my head and dealing with people pulling LCY to the entrance begin flashing. Ok, I'm gonna forget it, wth, let's get on with it.<br><br>So, anyway, we are fighting back to disco when guard breaks! Ok, we'll take guard. We move into guard, go thru a cycle...then we run into trouble with a gater from exit, and when we go to pull from beyond bridge, all of exit agros..so we have to succor, no biggie. Nobody in exit, no harm done, we begin workin back to camp, we get an LD, so we wait a sec. I go around the corner from rock, and there is Alwayyz, kinda hangin out, waitin for a shammy friend, at guard. My cleric tells him that we are coming back to guard, just waiting on a LD. Well, his buddy gets over to him, and the named beetle is right there...our group watches as they pull the Named! Attaboy! WTG!! I run over and say &quot; Thanks for pulling for us, but we can handle it&quot; and of course they have to play like &quot;What? this mob? oh, yea, well, um..&quot; I ask Alwayyz if he cares that he is campstealing..&quot;Nope&quot;. Then afterwards, when my group is all at guard, even the LD..Alwayyz 'graciously' offers to give us the &quot;shitty vambraces that dropped&quot;..More cursing from  my direction..another &quot;Chill out dude&quot;....I'm sorry, is this game now composed of classless pinheads? Should I even bother investing more time here, or is this game a lost cause? 3 years, maybe all the good people have left, leaving us with this &quot;second generation&quot; of cretins who've just been released from Juvy? I don't know...I just wanted to share this, and for those of you who have moved to Charassis to avoid it...THEY'RE COMING! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ubburlydorf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BBurlydorf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 117<br> <font color=#333333>(7/9/02 6:35:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=657.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Sebilis-The death of a fine zone (</span><hr size=1> Seb has always been a mixed bag.<br><br>On the one hand it's one of the zones people go to when they move beyond KC. A low 50's group can hunt there, but not in complete safety. Even getting to a camp can become an ordeal. As a result, the zoneline and Exit can turn into a death trap with inexperianced players trying to run for safety.<br><br>At higher levels it's possible to do camps that are out of the way of trains and long-distance pullers. But King, Juggs/Reets, and Crypt can go badly and CR can suck big time.<br><br>Mid-50 players are tempted to bite off more they can chew.<br><br>High level players tend to do high-exp camps and pull everything they can reach. (Camping Guard it's not uncommon to pull Exit, Necro Jail, etc.). Alternately they either solo or partner an easy camp.<br><br>IMO if there are 36 or more players in Seb and you can't handle King, Juggs/Reets, or Crypt (or they're camped) it's time to find another zone.<br><br>Seb is a great indoor zone with camps suitable for various levels. Inexperianced players, high level players doing mid-level camps, and overcrowding are to my mind the only problems.<br><br>Try Maiden's Eye if you want to see the circus. The clowns alone are worth the price of admission.<br><br>BB<br>Battleblade Burlydorf<br>60 Warrior <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uxoralundra.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xoralundra</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Badass Barbarian Shaman</span><br>  Posts: 1030<br> <font color=#333333>(7/9/02 6:52:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=657.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.alexander.darkwave.org.uk/lobo.jpg height=100 width=75 ></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sebilis-The death of a fine zone (</span><hr size=1> Quick translation for those that couldn't be bothered.<br><br>You said:<br><br>1) Morin pulled some mobs for his group and we were in the way.<br>2) We couldn't handle guard and were suprised when someone else had taken it when we had to succor out.<br><br>As far as I can see, this translates into...<br><br>1) A single Monk &gt; Our Whole Group<br>2) We expect people to respect our camp after we leave it.<br><br>I suggest you think twice before starting a flame war for such weak reasons, because you haven't really said anything that puts you in the right, a