ach other the time of day were exploring the place together and trying to figure out what went where.<br><br>The zone ceased to be the same zone it once was when camps took over.  Camps suck.  They take the skill out of the game.  Unfortunately it's just the nature of the beast I suppose.  Lower Guk was one hell of a fun zone until such a time as you could zone into the dead side of the zone and run all the way to the live side castle without seeing a single living frog.  The zone changed due to the same reasons Sebilis is changing:  People gained levels and started staking out little bits and pieces of the dungeon.<br><br>I always thought the game was much more fun when 6 skilled players had the outside chance of getting their collective butts beat into the ground on a bad pull.  Seems to me they need to add the crawl back to the game.  The crawl is what makes the game fun.  That's what made the trip down to visit the queen in Chardok fun.  That's what made the trip to kill Trakanon fun.  It's also what made the trip to kill Lord Yelinak fun.  When we killed stuff with KEG, we always did the crawl with at least the first few groups for a raid.  We didn't screw around with the whole &quot;camp a CoH mage at the cubby hole&quot; thing.  We fought our way there.  That was fun.<br><br>Wish they'd add more zones for people to do these types of crawls.  If you've never been part of a group doing a dungeon crawl to defeat a boss mob somewhere, I think you've missed out on one of the most fun things you can do in the game.<br><br>Velks leveling be damned, even the run to Velkator and Lord Dojomustard was fun.  It was very cool seeing what a zone had to throw at you and seeing if you could defeat it.<br> <p><center><table border="1" bordercolor="#000000" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="0"><tr><td align="center" valign="center"><font face="Verdana, sans-serif" size="2"><strong> Lewick Goodheart</strong></br></font>Warder<BR>Final Uprising<BR>Zebuxoruk 